The State files an Amended Information which charges one count of expose child to harmful material, contrary to section 948.11(2)(a) and one count of contributing to the delinquency of a child, contrary to Section 948.40(1).
NO CONTEST pleas entered to both counts in the Amended Information.  Convicted.
On count 1, Sentence is wthheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling and deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Sex Offender Registry compliance;
3) Any contact with minors will be at the agents discretion, excluding family members who are children;
4) Use of Internet enabled devices will be at the agents discretion with the exception of employment purposes and functions;
5) Maintain fulltime employment;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) provide DNA sample;
9) complete one hundred (100) hours of community service within the first year of probation.
On count 2, the defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for thirty (30) days, under the Huber Law, commencing on 07-12-16 by 5:00 p.m.
$355.00 court costs imposed, to be paid by 08-28-16 or 7 days county jail for failure to pay.
Minutes.
